<h1>About ampm Pro Audio</h1>
<p>ampm Pro Audio is built to supply the tools needed for next-level sound.</p>

<h2>Project Data Sources</h2>
<p>The data driving this application is generated using the <strong>Faker</strong> gem, acting as the primary data source to simulate a live e-commerce environment. It populates:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Inventory:</strong> 80 unique products across 8 categories (e.g., Mixers, Turntables, Studio Monitors).</li>
  <li><strong>Transactions:</strong> 50 unique customer profiles and their associated order histories.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Database Architecture</h2>
<p>The backend is structured around a custom Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD), utilizing Active Record to manage multiple one-to-many and many-to-many associations between Categories, Products, Customers, and Orders.</p>